Battlefield 3 released in October of 2011. New gameplay mechanics like suppression and vaulting brought the series to a new level of immersion. Large levels, detailed destruction and robust weapon customization paved the way for the future of the series. And of course, it also gave us Operation Métro.

BRANI ISLAND, SINGAPORE.

For years, rising sea levels and increased storm patterns suggested dire consequences for the shipping industry on Brani Island. Rather than accepting this fate, the Singaporean government chose to tackle the problem and initiated the massive SeaWall project. The port thrives today and is heavily relied upon as a key part of America’s supply network.

Russia targets the port as a key strategic location and launches an offensive, but America moves quickly to repel enemy forces and protect their interests in the region.
Battle for control of a single alternating objective. Redeploying is disabled while owning the objective.
Boots on the ground is our top priority. Enjoy Conquest with limited vehicles and more ground combat!

Battlefield™ 2042 is a first-person shooter that marks the return to the iconic all-out warfare of the franchise. In a near-future world transformed by disorder, adapt and overcome dynamically-changing battlegrounds with the help of your squad and a cutting-edge arsenal.

Timely delivery of Health and Ammo crates are an essential part of sustaining battlefield operations. After an engagement your teammates will inevitably be low on ammunition, and probably health. A well-placed crate can replenishment both, allowing friendly forces to regroup and push on to the next objective. Prioritize support crates within your squad so everyone can stay in the fight, and keep an eye out for other friendlies in need of a few bullets and bandages.

Fireteam Exodus moved in silence, but they were all thinking the same thing: justice was at hand. 
 
 Oz’s betrayal and attack on Exodus. The satellite at Doha that started the war. The assault on Black Ridge. It all came down to what Oz was building, right here: a weapon of mass destruction.
  
 Oz had manipulated too many No-Pats to his cause. This was their chance to change that, before it was too late.
 
 Don’t forget what you’re fighting for.

The room was silent. The listening device Wolff had planted on Fireteam Exodus caught everything. He’d recorded the entire confrontation with Oz’s operative.
 
 Silver Spear within his grasp… and Zain had lured them away. The possibility Exodus had been compromised was real. 
 
 “What’s the play, sir?” an officer asked.
 
 Maybe there was still an opportunity here.
  
 “Wake up Director Renoit.”
 
 In twenty minutes, with every operable TOR locked in battle, Nordvik would be obliterated. He needed to move fast.

For those looking to balance firepower and accuracy, the designated marksman rifle (DMR) enables controlled semi-automatic fire at range. Typically designed with extended barrels and specialized, high-velocity rounds, the DMR is deadly in the hands of soldiers capable of tight shot groups. Whether you want to mix it up at the front with your squad or counter pesky enemy snipers, a variety of attachments permits the creation of a weapon that fits your play style.

Petya Boris Guskovsky is the brash and cocky weapons expert on the team. From Omsk, Russia. Rose from a hard life of physical labour and military disappointment to become a wealthy, global arms dealer. He is demanding and pushy because he knows that he is always right. Became a No-Pat when he had to go on the run because of a business deal gone bad. Believes that the world is unfair so you must look out for yourself.
Find the Battlefield experience that's right for you by browsing a variety of game modes created by the community.
Loadout Crates Called In as Angel

An ex-military survivalist, Webster MacKay is an ass-kicker with a conscience. Born on base in Cold Lake, Alberta, he was raised by a single father and was a classic army brat. Having lost his mother and moving constantly, he became more and more of a loner, comfortable relying on himself. Joined the No-Pats when he realized how much he and his survival skills could help. As a lone wolf, he will follow his gut before he waits for orders.
The battleground is a hazardous place in 2042. Suit up and become the ultimate threat to your enemy’s health.
Bring the enemy down to absolute zero and shatter their defenses while moving like a ghost through the battlefield.

The CG Recoilless M5 provides a handheld ability to destroy a wide range of enemy equipment and fortifications. Maneuver on the flanks to deliver kill-shots on unsuspecting armor, or fire well-placed rounds through windows (or walls) to ruin the day of everyone inside. Be sure to maintain plenty of distance - the explosion on the receiving end is sizable.
Terrors lie in wait for the right time to strike. Rise up and submerge the opposition.

Battlefield: Bad Company 2 released in March of 2010. Bad Company was the first game of the series to feature a single player campaign, and the sequel retained the same focus on a light-hearted tone and entertaining characters. Bad Company also introduced environmental destruction, setting the standard for the rest of the series.

Born to a wealthy family in Gdańsk, Lis never wanted for anything, and the trade-off was a future entirely mapped out for her. Rebelling, she sought the challenge and comradeship of military service and excelled, quickly entering Poland’s elite special forces. The collapse of Europe saw her life upended, and her unit destroyed. But a call from an old friend inviting her to join the No-Pats gives her a reason to fight again and the chance to rebuild her life.

Oz made a deal with the Dark Market. Black Ridge… it’s connected. Listen. The Dark Market cannot be trusted. They have control <STATIC> both East and West. Weapons, mercenaries, intelligence <STATIC> sell anything to the highest bidder. They are everywhere.

Confident, fun, and cool under pressure, Navin Rao is the Task Force’s tech specialist. Born and raised in Mumbai, he was sickly as a teenager. While bedridden, Rao fell in with a hacker community where he learned coding, friendship, and teamwork. At 21, he joined the Indian Armed Forces and eventually was selected for the elite MARCOS. Joined the No-Pats after being blamed for a refugee op that went south. Curious and inventive.

With increased range, powerful rounds and a relatively high rate of fire, assault rifles are ideal for static short and midrange engagements. Adjust fire modes to find the right balance between accuracy and effective suppression. Best when used in open terrain, but will get the job done in close quarters as well. High damage output means hitting your targets will typically incapacitate them, but be sure to manage your ammunition and consider a quick transition to sidearm in order to finish the job.

KOUROU, FRENCH GUIANA. 

Once a shining example of international cooperation and goodwill. After years of instability throughout the region the facility was completely abandoned. But since the Blackout of 2040, America's need for a launch site has triggered a quiet return to operations. 

The Americans race to complete their launch, or risk the tech falling into Russian hands. The Russians are determined to stop the launch by any means necessary. The site has been evacuated, and the military presence builds as the automated countdown continues.

Whether you are assaulting an enemy strongpoint or pinned down by enemy fire, there is rarely a bad time to reach for a fragmentation grenade. Pull the pin and toss in the general direction of the threat. An accurately-thrown grenade will take out enemy combatants sheltering behind obstacles, small knolls, or inside tight doors/windows and trenches. Be sure to consider the proper trajectory and take into account the 5-second fuse. Errant throws may have unintended consequences.

EASTERN DESERT, EGYPT.

In the mid-2030s, bio-tech giant Synseco Agritech, engineered a method to turn barren land arable, the by-products of which were highly weaponizable and valuable. Synseco became a target of repeated raids, in response to which a heavily fortified wall was erected around the facility.

The US moves on the site claiming Russian involvement and the arming of its allies in the region, but Russia hits back, unwilling to allow Synseco’s secrets to fall into enemy hands.

Air superiority is critical to any ground operation. As the pilot of an attack aircraft your first job is to help clear the skies of enemy threats, then capitalize by unleashing devasting fire on vulnerable ground targets. Understanding the situation on the ground is critical, so keep your eyes and ears open for hotspots and requests for close air support. Use ATGMs to take out tanks, and rockets or cannons to annihilate scurrying infantry and light vehicles.

Ideal for close quarter fights in which there are multiple targets and fire volume is critical. Usually designed for smaller pistol cartridges, submachine guns trade range for a high rate of fire and maximum damage. Light Combat Vehicles sacrifice protection for speed and mobility. Use them for lightning assaults and extractions or to harass the enemy’s flanks. Minimize risks to passengers by quickly delivering them to their destination. Mounted weapon systems can serve as a combat multiplier to a dismounted squad on the move, so be sure to coordinate engagements. You will have a target on your back the moment you arrive on the battlefield, so remember, constant movement is key to survival. Engage and displace.

The introverted and anti-social Wikus “Casper” Van Daele is something of a walking contradiction. Solitary by nature, he is fiercely loyal to those he considers his friends. Born in Cape Town, South Africa, Casper turned to nature and distance running to manage his anxiety and depression. Became a member of the 5 Special Forces Regiment before moving to MONUSCO peacekeeping missions. Has experienced the pain of global refugees first hand when his entire family was killed by the Cape Town tsunami.

Dr. Maria Falck is a highly-trained medic and trauma surgeon. Born in Cologne, Germany, she has the most experience—military, career, life—than any other Task Force member. She cares about people and doing what is right but she won’t take shit from anyone. She joined the team, after receiving word that her missing son David had been seen among the No-Pats. She believes that tragedy and evil exist, but there is always something that good people can do.
